name: Syrian Serin
rangeDescription: Mountains of lebanon and syria; winters to türkiye and northwestern iraq
description: A small and elegant finch. More elongated than European Serin and much plainer.

name: Buru Mountain-Pigeon
rangeDescription: Montane forest of buru (southern moluccas)
description: A large pigeon confined to Buru. Shows a pale gray crown and nape, slate-gray upperparts, and a cream throat and breast becoming salmon-pink on the belly.

name: Moluccan Hanging-Parrot
rangeDescription: Northern moluccas (halmahera and bacan)
description: A tiny, short-tailed green parrot with a narrow red throat patch and a vivid red rump. Males show a red forecrown and pale eye.

name: Seychelles Fody
rangeDescription: Seychelles islands (cousin, cousine, and frégate)
description: An unusual drab, long-billed fody. Breeding males have yellow patches on the face.

name: Black Thrush
rangeDescription: Humid montane forest of eastern, southeastern and southern mexico to northwestern nicaragua
description: Uncommon thrush of humid evergreen and pine-evergreen forest in highlands. Feeds mainly in fruiting trees and bushes, often with other thrushes; rarely feeds on the ground.

name: Forster's Tern
rangeDescription: North america; winters southern usa to costa rica and greater antilles
description: Smaller than all the gulls, with thinner and more pointed bill. Distinguished from other terns by pale whitish wings and orange-based bill in summer, and isolated black ear patch in winter.

name: Striated Lorikeet
rangeDescription: Mountains of western new guinea (snow mountains to chimbu province)
description: A rare, medium-sized lorikeet of foothill and lower montane forest. Green body with yellow-green striations on the face and underparts, and a gray band from the eye around the back of the head.

name: Samar Crow
rangeDescription: Southern philippines (samar and mindanao)
description: Uncommon small black crow. Plumage has an iridescent dark blue sheen when seen up close.

name: Visayan Broadbill
rangeDescription: Central philippines (leyte, samar, and bohol)
description: A medium-sized bird of lowland forest on Bohol, Leyte, and Samar islands. Has a pale blue bill and deeper blue eye wattle, a black face, a streaked crown, a reddish-brown back, a dark wing with a pinkish to white wingbar, a thin white collar with some scaling above, and a reddish rump and tail.

name: Yellow-lored Tanager
rangeDescription: Tropical southern colombia to central bolivia (la paz eastward to western santa cruz)
description: Large and chunky with stout dark bill. Nondescript plumage: entirely olive-green with slightly brighter yellowish throat and upper breast.

name: Tamaulipas Pygmy-Owl
rangeDescription: Northeastern mexico (southwestern tamaulipas, eastern san luis potosí, and northern hidalgo)
description: Very small owl of tropical forest in the foothills of northeast Mexico where it is endemic. Favors forest canopy and is rarely seen, but sometimes hunts low at edges; active in the daytime.

name: Gray Emutail
rangeDescription: Humid grassy swamps of eastern madagascar
description: Medium-sized, gray-brown bird with a weird spiky tail. Dull streaking on the back and underparts.

name: White-masked Antbird
rangeDescription: Northeastern peru (lower río pastaza and lower río morona)
description: Handsome antbird known only from a small area in northeastern Peru. Restricted to lowland rainforest in areas where the soil is sandy.

name: Gray-capped Cuckoo
rangeDescription: Northern colombia and northern venezuela; migrates to western peru
description: Brightly-colored cuckoo found mainly west of the Andes. Combination of rufous-tawny body and gray separates it from other cuckoos in range.

name: Uniform Treehunter
rangeDescription: Humid western andes of colombia and western ecuador (southward to el oro)
description: Medium-sized brownish bird of the lower subtropical zone in the western Andes of Colombia and Ecuador. Plain dark brown with much less streaking than other treehunters; only shows a slightly paler eyebrow and some streaking on the throat.

name: Sooty Shearwater
rangeDescription: Breeds southern south america, new zealand, and southeastern australia; winters to north pacific and north atlantic
description: Medium-sized, dark brown shearwater with silvery flashes on underwings. Narrow wings with quick, deep wingbeats.

name: Marsh Babbler
rangeDescription: Northeastern india (arunachal pradesh to cachar, khasi, and chittagong hills)
description: A small, mostly brown bird with a heavily streaked pale breast. Note the white eyebrow, the white throat, and the rusty flanks and belly.

name: Ochraceous-breasted Flycatcher
rangeDescription: East slope of andes of eastern peru (amazonas) to western bolivia (la paz)
description: Fairly small yellow-orange flycatcher that perches upright in humid montane forest. Olive brown above and warm yellowish orange below with white wingbars.

name: Teardrop White-eye
rangeDescription: Forest and scrub of chuuk (eastern caroline islands)
description: Strange-looking bird with a tiny range, found exclusively on the islands of Tol South, Onei, Paata, and Polle, in Chuuk, Micronesia. Only in dense native old-growth montane forest, where it is often found close to the endemic poison tree (“panaw” in Chuukese).

name: Fiery-browed Myna
rangeDescription: Mountains of sulawesi
description: An unmistakable, long-tailed, conspicuous myna with a broad orange eyebrow, a pale eye, an ash-gray body, mossy green wings and tail, and a contrasting yellowish rump. Juvenile browner, with a narrower eyebrow and a dark eye.
